- !<ScriptComponent/ddc4f975-fa22-4409-8001-7cfa360e683b>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: CardQueryVoiceAgent
  Enabled: true
  ScriptAsset: !<reference> 5238106c-5e3e-4b44-9b5e-27195870dc2b
  ScriptInputsDefault:
    autoStart: true
    model: true
    enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypesDefault:
    {}
  ScriptInputs:
    "":
      websocketRequirementsObj: !<reference.SceneObject> 0fc53fdb-e0c9-4876-9997-27447c597c4f
      dynamicAudioOutput: !<MappingBased.AssignableType> f53fb092-b740-4038-84d4-0c8f01e84a1e
      microphoneRecorder: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_1> 2233c94e-ea2f-4926-977e-b0100c676fac
      cardDeck: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_2> c99be548-d91a-4909-b4fb-8e0e02d53858
      globeController: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_3> 05388fb0-0dde-44c7-a8c9-1f6a6bb35ced
      autoStart: true
      voice: Leda
      persona: |-
        You help the user find AR trivia cards floating in a deck above a globe. When they describe what they want, call query_cards with the location, topic, date range, and/or keyword you extract, and say a short warm line like 'Gotcha — finding those now!'. If query_cards returns zero cards, ask ONE short clarifying question; if the next try still finds nothing,
          DROP your least-certain keyword and query again, briefly narrating each step so the user follows along. When it returns cards, summarize how many and where (e.g. 'I found 3 cards captured in Tokyo!'). If some matches can't be shown (unshown > 0), mention that. After results, the user may ask about the card they're looking at — I will tell you which card thatis; do NOT bring it up or speak about it until they actually ask. Keep replies to one to three warm sentences. To start over or undo, call clear_query.
      model: gemini-live-2.5-flash
      enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypes:
    "":
      {}
- !<ScriptComponent/de193d8a-4469-437c-9731-b1ebbba3002a>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: WelcomeVoice
  Enabled: true
  ScriptAsset: !<reference> 4ddc9c37-66f8-4dcf-a081-57727d7d76c8
  ScriptInputsDefault:
    greetingIntent: true
    interestsIntentTemplate: true
    delaySeconds: true
    persona: true
    enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypesDefault:
    {}
  ScriptInputs:
    "":
      websocketRequirementsObj: !<reference.SceneObject> 0fc53fdb-e0c9-4876-9997-27447c597c4f
      dynamicAudioOutput: !<MappingBased.AssignableType> 56d4b1d9-f137-4f41-8c54-c2efaf037961
      voice: Leda
      greetingIntent: "Warmly welcome the user to TriviaGo. Say you're excited to learn and explore the world together with them. Then invite them to tell you a little about themselves and what they're interested in. Keep it to about two short, natural sentences."
      interestsIntentTemplate: "The user just chose these interests: {topics}. React thoughtfully (a little \"hmm, I see\"), then say that based on those interests you've found some places they might enjoy, and ask if they'd like to take a look. About two short, natural sentences."
      delaySeconds: !<float> 5.000000
      persona: "You are the warm, upbeat first-person voice host of TriviaGo, an AR learning companion. You speak directly to the user. When given an instruction about what to convey, say it in your own words -- one or two short, natural, friendly sentences -- and vary the wording. Never read instructions back, never add stage directions or quotation marks, and don't ask for clarification; just speak naturally to the user."
      model: gemini-live-2.5-flash
      enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypes:
    "":
      {}
